OL,3,CVoters in the North West have their
OL,4,Csay ahead of local elections
OL,6,FNational trends have seen the country
OL,7,Fmoving away from two-party politics,
OL,8,Fand Bolton, Oldham and Stockport are
OL,9,Fones to watch specifically, as no
OL,10,Fparty has an outright majority there.
OL,12,FSefton and St Helens in Merseyside and
OL,13,FBurnley and Pendle in Lancashire will
OL,14,Falso be difficult to call.
OL,16,FResidents are split on what issues
OL,17,Fwill influence their vote the most.
OL,18,FOne mum - who has a family of five
OL,19,Fchildren in Greater Manchester - said
OL,20,Fthe most important issue for her is
OL,21,Fthe general cost of living.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776445554
OL,3,CVoters in the North West have their
OL,4,Csay ahead of local elections
OL,6,FShe said: "I don't think our wages are
OL,7,Freplicating now how much the cost of
OL,8,Fliving is."
OL,10,FThese local elections could have
OL,11,Flarger implications on politics
OL,12,Fnationally, and it could give us some
OL,13,Findication on how well Labour will do
OL,14,Fat the next General Election.
OL,16,FOne man said he is conflicted on
OL,17,Fvoting on local or national issues. He
OL,18,Fsaid: "I'm in two minds about whether
OL,19,Fto vote Labour. I've certainly been
OL,20,Fattracted by the Green Party recently
OL,21,Fand their recent gains.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
